    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "> I did originally look at trying to form a URL on submit and then simply just redirect to that.\n\nYes this is the way to go for now indeed. But you could also completely replace the homepage content and use instantsearch.js on the homepage as if it was a search page.\n\nMaybe what you could try is this:\n\n``` js\nvar search = instantsearch({\n  searchFunction: function() {\n    var queryString = search.helper.getStateAsQueryString();\n    // redirect to queryString\n  },\n....\n})\n```\n\nLet me know how it goes. \n",
    "created_at": "2016-10-04T20:21:46Z",
    "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/1378#issuecomment-251501454",
